European Stocks Drop After Japanese Earthquake, ECB Interest-Rate Increase

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-04-07T15:34:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/european-stocks-drop-after-japanese-earthquake-ecb-interest-rate-increase.html
European stocks fell for the first
time in five days after a 7.4-magnitude earthquake struck off
the coast of  Japan  and the  European Central Bank  raised interest
rates for the first time in almost three years.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index declined 0.2 percent to 280.9 at
4:34 p.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  